fields.physical_description:
plain house with a deep sloping roof
[Base board] base board, chip board covered with grey melamine and a wood grain patterned laminate
[Frame] right side frame, maple wood, with vertical groove and countersuck screw holes
[Frame] left side frame, matching B.245:2-1998
[Wall] right side rear wall, pine frame with cearm coloured melamine wall panel; screw holes
[Wall] left side rear wall to match B.245:4-1998
[Angle] reinforement angle, wood
[Angle] as B.245:6-1998
[Floor] second storey floor, matcing the base, B.245:1-1998; square hole with slots cut from centre for the interior walls
[Panel] interior wall panel, matching rear walls, B.245:4,5-1998; 2 door holes cut out trimmed with pine, various slots and grooves
[Panel] as B.245:9-1998, with no door openings
[Panel] interior wall panel, chipboard covered with cream melamine
[Floor] attic floor, chipboard covered with cream melamine and wood grain laminate edge
[Roof] chipboard with red melamine and wood grain laminate; hinged and bevel cut at centre to fold into place
[Staircase] staircase, lower half with 4 steps and landing, plywood covered with cream melamine; with two pegs for fastening
[Staircase] staircase upper half, matching the lower part with the exception of the depth
[Glue] tube of wood glue with the text on the back in German
